1
00:00:13,613 --> 00:00:15,749
Geonwoo, are you awake...?

2
00:00:23,456 --> 00:00:25,892
What's the deal with you two?

3
00:00:28,762 --> 00:00:31,698
Don't tell me... are you
guys actually dating?

4
00:00:35,869 --> 00:00:37,871
Should we be?

5
00:00:39,105 --> 00:00:41,107
From this moment on.

6
00:01:06,866 --> 00:01:08,168
Let's start.

7
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:12,238
Come on.

8
00:01:23,149 --> 00:01:24,917
Dad...

9
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:26,920
Taewoo...

10
00:01:27,554 --> 00:01:29,556
Geonwoo.

11
00:01:35,495 --> 00:01:39,432
Back then... I think I was out of my mind.

12
00:01:41,167 --> 00:01:43,268
After the divorce,

13
00:01:43,269 --> 00:01:45,839
I just started hating the whole world.

14
00:01:46,406 --> 00:01:49,476
Taewoo, I really let you down.

15
00:01:51,478 --> 00:01:53,178
Geonwoo...

16
00:01:53,179 --> 00:01:56,015
I have no excuse for what I did.

17
00:01:58,017 --> 00:01:59,586
So...

18
00:01:59,919 --> 00:02:02,956
I just ran away.

19
00:02:03,823 --> 00:02:07,494
But seeing you both doing so well...

20
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:10,129
I'm just so grateful.

21
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:14,901
I was afraid my guilt would
only weigh you down again,

22
00:02:15,668 --> 00:02:18,671
so I couldn't find the
courage to reach out.

23
00:02:20,473 --> 00:02:23,943
But you're still our dad. Let's
stay in touch from now on.

24
00:02:25,545 --> 00:02:27,847
Yeah, let's keep in contact, Dad.

25
00:02:36,256 --> 00:02:37,724
Jaeyeon... thank you.

26
00:02:37,924 --> 00:02:39,391
This is all thanks to you.

27
00:02:39,392 --> 00:02:41,493
I didn't do anything.

28
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:42,995
Taewoo's right.

29
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:46,299
I wouldn't have had
the courage without you.

30
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:49,636
So you two are a thing now, right?

31
00:02:50,370 --> 00:02:51,771
Yeah.

32
00:02:52,205 --> 00:02:54,240
I guess that's how it turned out.

33
00:02:55,408 --> 00:02:56,708
You guys actually look
pretty good together.

34
00:02:56,709 --> 00:02:58,443
Well, obviously.

35
00:02:58,444 --> 00:03:00,813
You're still a total jerk, though.

36
00:03:01,981 --> 00:03:03,983
You want to die?

37
00:03:08,221 --> 00:03:10,256
I need to take this call.

38
00:03:15,828 --> 00:03:17,496
I'm sorry about what happened that day.

39
00:03:17,497 --> 00:03:18,964
Huh?

40
00:03:18,965 --> 00:03:21,099
For kissing you without asking.

41
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:23,069
Oh... uh... hey...

42
00:03:24,437 --> 00:03:26,205
I don't even remember that.

43
00:03:26,206 --> 00:03:28,541
Why are you still dwelling on it?

44
00:03:28,675 --> 00:03:30,577
I like you.

45
00:03:32,178 --> 00:03:35,548
I've liked you since we were kids,
even before you can remember.

46
00:03:39,285 --> 00:03:41,387
But I'm not going to anymore.

47
00:03:41,621 --> 00:03:42,455
Taewoo...

48
00:03:42,456 --> 00:03:44,056
We're friends.

49
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:45,757
The best of friends.

50
00:03:45,758 --> 00:03:48,294
Closer than family.

51
00:03:48,962 --> 00:03:49,962
Yeah.

52
00:03:49,963 --> 00:03:52,298
That'll never change.

53
00:03:53,032 --> 00:03:55,101
Give me a hug.

54
00:04:00,006 --> 00:04:01,741
Hey!

55
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:04,810
What do you think you're
doing with my boyfriend?

56
00:04:04,811 --> 00:04:06,745
You really want to die, don't you?

57
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:09,549
You're so possessive,
Jaeyeon's gonna run away.

58
00:04:10,016 --> 00:04:11,149
Really?

59
00:04:11,150 --> 00:04:14,286
No, what are you even worried about?

60
00:04:14,287 --> 00:04:16,355
Fine, I hope you two
live happily ever after.

61
00:04:16,356 --> 00:04:18,824
I'll just take my cue and leave.

62
00:04:18,825 --> 00:04:21,059
Aren't you staying for dinner?

63
00:04:21,060 --> 00:04:23,061
Nah, I'm busy.

64
00:04:23,062 --> 00:04:24,263
Get home safe.

65
00:04:24,264 --> 00:04:26,266
Yeah, see ya.

66
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,946
Why...?

67
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:43,382
You let Taewoo hug you.

68
00:04:43,383 --> 00:04:46,452
That's different. You're an actor...

69
00:04:48,087 --> 00:04:49,989
If you're so worried about getting caught,

70
00:04:50,023 --> 00:04:52,592
do you want to go to my place?

71
00:05:02,535 --> 00:05:04,002
Hi, Geonwoo.

72
00:05:04,003 --> 00:05:06,972
I heard you went to Cannes this time.

73
00:05:06,973 --> 00:05:09,207
I have to ask how it went.

74
00:05:09,208 --> 00:05:10,709
Before we get into that,

75
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:13,279
why don't we take a look at the trailer?

76
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:15,485
That summer...

77
00:05:15,866 --> 00:05:17,091
(That Summer)

78
00:05:17,116 --> 00:05:19,118
we were young and foolish.

79
00:05:19,585 --> 00:05:21,888
But that's why we were fearless.

80
00:05:22,288 --> 00:05:24,790
Even if we could go back to that day,

81
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:26,793
knowing everything we know now,

82
00:05:35,435 --> 00:05:38,604
would we still run to each other?

83
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,500
(A time-loop queer romance)
"That Summer"

84
00:05:48,525 --> 00:05:51,818
(Directed by Ryu Jeong-hyeok | Starring
Kim Geonwoo, Lee Jaeyeon)

85
00:05:52,118 --> 00:05:56,088
So, I heard this movie is a gay love story.

86
00:05:56,089 --> 00:05:57,989
How did that feel for you?

87
00:05:57,990 --> 00:05:59,057
Yes.

88
00:05:59,058 --> 00:06:02,694
It's a film by a director I deeply respect.

89
00:06:02,695 --> 00:06:04,663
And for this project,

90
00:06:04,664 --> 00:06:06,665
I treated it as a tribute

91
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:09,968
to my own personal muse.

92
00:06:09,969 --> 00:06:13,639
Maybe that's why the
response has been so great.

93
00:06:15,174 --> 00:06:19,145
That muse must be very happy.

94
00:06:23,342 --> 00:06:26,812
You guys should just go public already.

95
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:31,991
Feeling lonely?

96
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:35,294
Taewoo, don't be like that...

97
00:06:36,529 --> 00:06:38,998
It's just nice to see them so happy.

98
00:06:45,905 --> 00:06:48,341
Maybe we should try it sometime.

99
00:07:02,889 --> 00:07:05,056
In the movie,

100
00:07:05,057 --> 00:07:07,660
their love doesn't work out in the end.

101
00:07:09,095 --> 00:07:11,897
My character gives in to family pressure,

102
00:07:11,898 --> 00:07:14,934
gets married, and has kids.

103
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:17,436
It's not until he's much older

104
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:20,740
that he meets his true love again.

105
00:07:21,407 --> 00:07:23,176
Really?

106
00:07:23,910 --> 00:07:26,045
That's so sad.

107
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:28,947
Well, that's not going to be us.

108
00:07:28,948 --> 00:07:31,984
We're staying together until we die.

109
00:07:32,652 --> 00:07:35,421
Should we go ahead and
order matching coffins?

110
00:07:38,191 --> 00:07:42,094
Okay, okay, I get it, Mr. Possessive.

111
00:07:44,096 --> 00:07:45,363
So,

112
00:07:45,364 --> 00:07:46,698
what are you doing tomorrow?

113
00:07:46,699 --> 00:07:48,467
- Tomorrow?
- Yeah.

114
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:50,535
I'll have to check with my manager.

115
00:07:50,536 --> 00:07:53,772
I think I have a shoot in Apgujeong.

116
00:07:53,773 --> 00:07:55,140
Apgujeong?

117
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:57,476
I thought that drama was already finished.

118
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:58,777
Not yet, there's a little bit left.

119
00:07:58,778 --> 00:08:00,246
I think they're doing some reshoots.

120
00:08:02,448 --> 00:08:05,618
Still, I'm glad I got to see you today.

121
00:08:06,219 --> 00:08:09,621
Why? What are you doing tomorrow?

122
00:08:09,622 --> 00:08:10,523
Me?

123
00:08:10,524 --> 00:08:12,390
I'm just a college student.

124
00:08:12,391 --> 00:08:13,959
I don't have class tomorrow,

125
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,126
and I've already finished all my work.

126
00:08:15,127 --> 00:08:15,728
Really?

127
00:08:15,729 --> 00:08:18,063
Then I'll be waiting for
my possessive boyfriend.

128
00:08:18,064 --> 00:08:21,233
Let's have dinner the
day after tomorrow, then.

129
00:08:21,234 --> 00:08:23,436
Sounds good.

130
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:25,571
Hey.

131
00:08:25,572 --> 00:08:27,073
Are you gonna buy me something good?

132
00:08:27,540 --> 00:08:28,540
You're paying!

133
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:37,000
"Fan Service"
(Episode 6)

